  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dd0\u0da2\u0dd2\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd3\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db4\u0db1\u0dd3 - \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db0\u0dcf\u0db1 \u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dba\u0dda \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db0\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0db6\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Rajina Pilipani - Disruption to train running on the main line",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported that the Rajarata Rajina Express Gami train running from Anuradhapura to Beliatta has derailed at the Polgahawela station and the train running on the main route has been disrupted and the passengers have been greatly inconvenienced.",
        "It is reported that the express train running from Kandy to Colombo Fort at 6.20 in the morning is also running with a delay of 1 hour 30 minutes with high passenger capacity and the train is being stopped midway.",
        "When Lankadeepa made a telephone call to the 1971 hotline regarding the derailment and train delay of the Rajarata Queen train, its officials directed us to Mr. Seneviratne, Deputy General Manager (Traffic), and since Mr. Seneviratne was not in the office, the office again called the 1971 hotline. We were directed.",
        "We were again referred to the General Manager's office, where an official who did not want to mention the name of the Railway General Manager's office said that although there may be a train delay at Polgahawela station, it will not affect the train running."
      ],
